BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:t346C8QfUOwYGghQzEHpc
SUMMARY:Whose Crit Is It\\\, Anyway?
DTSTAMP:20260307T061140Z
DTSTART:20260315T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Inspired by improv shows and Dungeons & Dragons\\\, Whose Crit 
	is It Anyway combines them into a performance with a cast of professional 
	actors that will take on the characters you create. Choose their adventure
	 and guide their actions\\\, and if you choose wisely\\\, they might even 
	survive!  \\nIf you’ve never played Dungeons & Dragons\\\, never fear\\\, 
	we’re using a simplified ruleset\\\, and we’ll have D&D veterans there to 
	guide you every step of the way. If you’re a veteran player yourself\\\, c
	ome experience a completely new way to play. \\nIn addition to having fun\
	\\, learn valuable writing and storytelling skills through the medium of D
	&D: \\nCollaborative Storytelling: Learn how to work together as part of a
	 creative team and how to draw inspiration from each other \\nCharacter De
	velopment: Get into the mind of your character and how they would act in v
	arious situations \\nImprovisation and Creativity: Stories can change as t
	he characters make decisions\\\, learn how to improvise and stay true to t
	he story\\\, even in the face of the unexpected \\nYour night will begin b
	y being divided into five groups\\\, one for each of our actors\\\, plus o
	ne that will help the Dungeon Master craft the experience. You will select
	 the abilities of the premade characters provided\\\, and then dive into t
	he story. Your suggestions can guide their actions\\\, which you’ll watch 
	them perform live on stage. With the input of the audience\\\, even our Du
	ngeon Master has no idea where this story might end up! \\nForge the Legen
	d! Get your tickets now! \\nMust be 18 years of age or older for entry.\n\
	nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-03-15/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-03-15/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
